{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_57","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"This change addresses issue #3591 by correcting the classification of `UBERON:0001629` (`carotid body`).\n\nRationale:\n- The cited source for the issue, PMID:32965908 (StatPearls / PubMed), describes the carotid body as a sensory organ in the peripheral nervous system located in the adventitia at the carotid bifurcation.\n- That supports an anatomical relation to the peripheral nervous system, not a `part_of` assertion to `UBERON:0001530` (`common carotid artery plus branches`).\n\nChanges made:\n- Removed `relationship: part_of UBERON:0001530 ! common carotid artery plus branches`.\n- Added `relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system` with a PMID:32965908 source.\n- Updated the textual definition to state that the carotid body is a chemoreceptive organ of the peripheral nervous system and added PMID:32965908 as a definition xref.\n- Added `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3591\" xsd:anyURI`.\n\nChecks completed:\n- Reviewed the imported issue title, body, and comments from `__issue_context__.json`.\n- Verified the current state of `UBERON:0001629` in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n- Checked relevant parent/context terms, including `UBERON:0001530`, `UBERON:0000010`, and `UBERON:0034979`.\n- Looked up PMID:32965908 via PubMed because the local `aurelian` command was not available in this environment.\n- Edited the checked-out term in `terms/`, checked it back into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`, and reserialized with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n\nValidation:\n- `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n\nLocal commit:\n- `a749319` `Fix carotid body classification`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
